has a message for those who persist in making methamphetamine: You
will be found. Your cooking laboratories will be seized. The proof,
agents believe, is in the numbers. Already this year, 193 meth labs
have been busted, more than in all of last year. And with agents
raiding two to three laboratories a day, the KBI expects to reach
the 500 mark before December. The surge is explained by the
wildfire spread of methamphetamine in rural areas, as well as
intensified law enforcement efforts. By DAWN BORMANN. Story will
move in the ``a'' category.
