   -----------------------------------------------
</P>
<P>
   The Millennium Series, six special issues of The New York Times
Magazine, is an unsurpassed journalistic celebration.
</P>
<P>
   Each issue explores a different, compelling theme, with
contributions from a stellar lineup of writers, photographers and
artists.
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times Syndicate will present packages from each
issue _ stories, photos and art. Ideal to enrich your own coverage
of the Millennium.
</P>
<P>
   FIRST UP: ``THE BEST OF THE MILLENNIUM.''
</P>
<P>
   (For descriptions of stories, see below.)
</P>
<P>
   Articles from this issue highlight the most important ideas,
inventions, creations and happenings of the last 1,000 years.
</P>
<P>
   Many of the stories feature LOCAL ANGLE boxes _ a new service
providing ideas and information to localize syndicated material.
</P>
