<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SFCHRONBUDG-SF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>


</HEADLINE>
 CHRON  These are the stories The San Francisco Chronicle Food section
plans to move Tuesday, April 27, on the New York Times News Service
wire. Questions? Please call Holly Ocasio Rizzo at 415-777-8811. &HT;     
 
 
San Francisco _  ROOTBEER  _ America is in the middle of a root
beer revolution, and a stream of the nation's oldest soda pop is
pouring through the Bay Area. We'll tell you who's drinking the new
microbeer root beers (hint: they include truck drivers, nostalgia
buffs and former beer drinkers) and why. 
With: 
 RTBEERFACTS:  A roundup of root beer facts; brief history of root
beer; root beer Web sites. 
 RTBEERFLOAT:  How an A&AMP;W owner and a San Francisco chef make root
beer floats; with recipes. 
 (Please also see TASTE-Root for The Chronicle's root beer taste 
 test.)  
 By Kim Severson  
 c. 1999 The San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
 &QL; 
San Francisco _  &UR; TASTE-Root  &LR; _ This week, The Chronicle's panel of
professional tasters rates bottled root beers. &QL; 
 &UR; By Robin Davis &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; c. 1999 The San Francisco Chronicle &QL;  &LR; 
 &QL; 
San Francisco _  &UR; FOODNEWS  &LR; _ After a late freeze, the artichoke
looked like a bust, but the weather turned around and so did the
crop. Prices and supply may be the best in years. &QL; 
