<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TV-MOVIE-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
`HOME MOVIES' IS THE LATEST IN THE NIGHTTIME TOON BOOM
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MATTHEW GILBERT  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
HOME MOVIES 
Starring the voices of: Paula Poundstone, Brendon Small, H. Jon
Benjamin  
On: UPN. The series begins its regular Monday at 8:30 timeslot
beginning next week.  
Rating: TVPG 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The nighttime toon boom continues Tuesday night with the
premiere of ``Home Movies,'' an animated sitcom from the producers
of Comedy Central's ``Dr. Katz: Professional Therapist.'' Each of
the new adult cartoons has its identifying mark _ ``Futurama'' is
from ``Simpsons'' creator Matt Groening, ``Dilbert'' is based on
the popular comic strip, ``The PJs'' is Eddie Murphy's
controversial vehicle _ and ``Home Movies'' is the one known for
featuring the voice of comedian Paula Poundstone. It's also the one
in Squigglevision, the minimalist animated style that seems to
quiver with anxiety.
</P>
<P>
   The promising main characters in ``Home Movies'' are Paula
Small, a clueless single mother in suburbia, and her amusing
8-year-old son Brendon, who is more psychologically sophisticated
than the adults around him. Brendon tends toward modern weariness,
and when the world is too much with him, he regresses and plays in
a sandbox ``to reflect on things.'' His favorite creative outlet is
making films on videotape, and ``Home Movies'' features a few of
his sloppy productions in each episode. With their half-formed
plots about cops and prisons and bombs, these small gems give voice
to Brendon's chaotic subconscious feelings while they send up the
baser cliches of pop culture.
</P>
<P>
   The show's mordant humor is appealing. It avoids the
over-the-top crudeness of ``Family Guy,'' another new animated
domestic sitcom, as it takes aim at the more Freudian foibles of
human behavior. The vocal rhythms recall the detached, self-aware,
and almost hypnotic rhythms that distinguish the wonderful ``Dr.
Katz.'' (H. Jon Benjamin, who gives voice to Jason and Coach
McGuirk, also plays Dr. Katz's son, Ben.) But let's hope the
writers find some original situations in which to showcase their
sensibility and their characters. In Tuesday night's episode,
Brendon goes into an Oedipal funk when he finds out that his mother
is dating his soccer coach, a vain lunkhead with brand-name tattoos
all over his body. Mom-on-a-date is a tired plot line, and it only
leads to predictable bits about Brendon trying to scare his
competition by calling him ``Dad'' and Paula withstanding a boring
dinner. Surely the Smalls would thrive in stranger places.
</P>
<P>
   ``Home Movies'' airs at 8:30 p.m. Next week, the show moves to
its regular time slot of Mondays at 8:30, after ``Dilbert.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
