<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-27 14:05 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A4987 &Cx1f; tab-z
r l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-RABBI-KOSOVO-ISRAEL-N     04-27 1037
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-RABBI-KOSOVO-ISRAEL-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
`NEVER FORGET' HAS DIFFERENT MEANINGS FOR SERBS, ISRAELIS 
</HEADLINE>
   (Commentary)  
<TEXT>
<P>
   (To purchase this ``separate buy'' article from the New York
Times Syndicate please contact syndicate sales representative DEBRA
WEYDERT at 732-390-4480) &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; By RABBI ELI HECHT &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   In a small European town there lived a sheriff who believed he
had solutions to all problems. One day a fire broke out. The
sheriff gave orders to form a fire brigade. A group of farmers
formed a line from the riverside to the burning house.
</P>
<P>
   Each farmer was given a pail to bring water to the burning
building. From hand to hand went the pail, quickly, until it
reached the first person close to the burning house. With a big
heave the water would be emptied on the fire.
</P>
<P>
   The sheriff observed that the fire was taking too long to be
extinguished. He decided to do something himself. He found a pail,
not realizing that it was full of gasoline, ran to the fire and
emptied the contents, thus engulfing the building and burning down
the town.
</P>
<P>
   This story reminds me of what is taking place in the Balkans and
how we are dealing with the problem. Instead of having an organized
approach to this terrible problem we seem to be pouring more and
more gasoline on the fire.
</P>
<P>
   NATO reports that more than 700,000 refugees are homeless.
Ethnic Albanian communities are gone. The so-called ethnic
Albanians pray for a miracle but none seems to be happening. The
more NATO bombs fall, the more the Serbs retaliate. The damage is
incomprehensible.
</P>
<P>
   Who is to blame for all of this?
</P>
<P>
   Evil Slobodan Milosevic is sticking to his plans. Kosovo will be
Serbian and rid of any ethnic Albanians. He claims that there
really is no Serb aggression, it is NATO that is the aggressor.
</P>
<P>
   Look here, he seems to say, we are fighting for statehood. All
countries and nationalities fight for statehood. All we want is our
homeland, Serbia, to be free of ethnic Albanians. If ethnic
cleansing means moving hundreds of thousands of people to other
countries, then we are guilty of that in the name of national
determination. We don't kill, he claims, we deport.
</P>
<P>
   He fools his people and the world, by stating that it is NATO
that has been killing people. The recent air attacks show that the
bombs have, indeed, fallen on innocent people. Each bomb causes
havoc and spreads death.
</P>
<P>
   It is no great miracle for NATO to bomb the land into the Stone
Age. It will, however, take a miracle to rebuild the land from the
Stone Age. Which ethnic Albanian in his right mind will want to
return to Kosovo? If and when they do, they won't blame Slobodan
Milosevic for the carnage, they will end up blaming NATO. Sad, but
true, it is Milosevic's plan that is now being carried out by NATO.
</P>
<P>
   Ironically it is NATO that is finding homes for the displaced
ethnic Albanians. Their organization for the resettlement of these
people guarantees Milosevic's plan of a Moslem-free Serbia.
</P>
<P>
   The Balkans have seen fighting for 600 years. They have inbred
hatred but have co-existed. Milosevic has fewer than 30,000 troops.
By involving NATO he has been able to put 700,000 people into
misery. He has caused the death of innocent people. It is so
unfortunate that he has been helped by our bombs.
</P>
<P>
   If anything, we should go after the man and not the country. By
bombing and destroying the land we galvanize the enemy and
antagonize the Russian neighbors.
</P>
<P>
   The answer to this dilemma is to find out how democratic
countries such as Israel deal with religious differences.
</P>
<P>
   Palestinians want a homeland. They want Israel's capital,
Jerusalem, to be their capital. This is no less than what is taking
place in Yugoslavia. Israel does not want that to happen.
</P>
<P>
   But does Israel bomb refugee camps? Do they ask America to call
in NATO to perform air strikes, destroy homes and displace the
people? No, Israel holds talks and then more talks and
negotiations. They meet in Oslo, they meet in France, in the White
House and in Jordan. They will do anything but have an outright
war.
</P>
<P>
   True, there are those who oppose the talks. There are those who
blow up buses and market places, but Israel does not do mass
deportations or ethnic cleansing. Israel searches out the
perpetrators and destroys only the perpetrators' homes. A strong
Israel does not take advantage of its superior military strength.
It does everything possible to keep the peace. The state of Israel
has chosen not to do what NATO is guilty of doing, killing and
bombing in the name of peace. They have chosen a more humane way to
deal with people who hate them, people who swear to drive them into
the sea.
</P>
<P>
   The Holocaust taught the Jewish state a very important lesson.
Never to forget what was done to them. To them the message of
``never forgetting'' leads to always forgiving.
</P>
<P>
   The Serbs have taken the message ``never to forget'' to mean
``never forgive.'' Now they repeat the same sins of their former
oppressors. They must be stopped.
</P>
<P>
   President Clinton said, ``We must follow the example of the
World War II generation by standing up to aggression and hate, and
then by following through with a post-conflict strategy for
reconstruction and renewal.''
</P>
<P>
   Clinton is pretty far off track. The World War II generation
lived through a war of untold proportions which was started by a
Hitler who had hundreds of thousands of soldiers with aspirations
to conquer the entire world.
</P>
<P>
   I know Milosevic's plans are bad for ethnic Albanians, but he is
no Hitler and, remember, displacement is not genocide. Milosevic is
one terrible man whom I despise deeply. But let us not help him win
his war.
</P>
<P>
   The Jewish state has shown us the path. They have the correct
way to deal with ethnic differences. It is leaderships that must be
replaced and not countries destroyed. It would do NATO good to
study Israel's policies and to learn from them.
</P>
<P>
   -----
</P>
<P>
   (Rabbi Eli Hecht is vice president of the Rabbinical Alliance of
America and director of Chabad of South Bay in Lomita, Calif.)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
