<P>
   ARK-INDICT (Little Rock, Ark.) _ The U.S. attorney in Little
Rock shakes the Arkansas political establishment by indicting a
large number of current and former members of the General Assembly.
The lawmakers, along with several prominent lobbyists, are charged
with handing out state contracts and grants to relatives and
friends. Although long expected, the indictments represent the
biggest political scandal in Arkansas in years, exposing the cozy
relationships between lawyers, lobbyists and legislators. They stem
from a report in a weekly newspaper two years ago. By David
Firestone.
