<P>
   Sports stories from The New York Times News Service for
 &UR; WEDNESDAY &LR; , April 38.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-VECSEY-COLUMN (Undated) _ Sports of The Times column on John
Franco, the left-handed reliever for the Mets who has compiled over
400 saves in a career remarkable for its longevity and resiliency.
By George Vecsey.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-METS-PADRES (New York) _ San Diego at Mets, 7:10 p.m. By
Jason Diamos.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-YANKS-RANGERS (Arlington, Texas) _ N.Y. Yankees at Texas,
8:35 p.m. ET start. Roger Clemens goes for his 18th straight
victory, which would set a new American League mark (the National
League mark is 23). By Buster Olney.
</P>
<P>
   HKN-DEVILS-PENGUINS (Pittsburgh) _ N.J. Devils at Pittsburgh,
7:35 p.m. ET start. By Alex Yannis.
</P>
