</P>
<P>
   LANGUAGE-COLUMN (Undated) _ Attributive, thy name is woman. By
Jan Freeman.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS (e) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   TV-MOVIE (Undated) -- ``Home Movies'' is the latest in the
nighttime toon boom. By Matthew Gilbert.
</P>
<P>
   BOOK-FURST (Undated) _ The slow growth of the French Resistance
is the subject of ``Red Gold,'' which may be Alan Furst's best
novel. By Richard Dyer.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; TRAVEL (t) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-SEDONA (Sedona, Ariz.) _ It was an unlikely, isolated
stop on our cross-country journey, far off the East-West
interstates, almost to the Left Coast, with a reputation for New
Age kookiness. By John Aloysius Farrell. 1285 words.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-COLUMN &UR;  &LR; (Undated) _ Traditions are one of the more
enjoyable aspects of Discovering America. By Jerry Morris.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-NOTES (Undated) _ Airports, despite their glitter, can be
boring places. Fortunately, many are near stellar attractions. By
Richard Carpenter.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-COLLINS (Stratford-upon-Avon, England) _ Who's
Shakespeare? The guy with the hots for Gwyneth Paltrow, is one
current answer. By Bud Collins.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   VIRUS-THREAT (Undated) _ Specialists say bugs like Chernobyl
could be avoided if computer users took precautions. By Ross
Kerber. 980 words. GRAPHIC: 35 picas x 3 inches, ``Computer
security incidents.''
</P>
<P>
   ONBUSINESS-COLUMN (Undated) _ Restauants lose appeal to
investors, so the company that runs Pizzeria Uno hires investment
bankers to explore its options. By Steven Syre and Charles Stein.
</P>
<P>
   WARSH-COLUMN (Undated) _ Under Bill Clinton's zigzag leadership
the Democrats have learned how to dominate the Senate by proving to
be more careful stewards of the Republican program than the GOP
itself. By David Warsh.
</P>
