   KOSOVO-TROOPS (Washington) _ A Military Analysis: Despite
spending billions of dollars through the '90s on ships and aircraft
meant to give the American military rapid global reach, the
Pentagon's effort in the Balkans has still struggled to overcome
the obstacles inherent in moving military might hundreds or
thousands of miles. By Eric Schmitt and Steven Lee Myers.
