<P>
   SCOTUS-BRIBE (Washington) _ The Supreme Court unanimously
rejects the expansive legal theory behind an independent counsel's
prosecution of former Agriculture Secretary Mike Espy and of those
who bestowed favors on him. Simply giving gifts to a federal
official, without any demonstrated connection to the official's
actions, does not violate the law, the court rules. By Linda
Greenhouse.
</P>
