held by former Speaker Robert Livingston. To keep Duke out, the
party is dusting off former Representative David Treen, now in his
70s, pledging that he can keep seniority. Have Republicans courted
the Southern right for so long that they have, effectively, asked
for a Duke candidacy? By Kevin Sack.
</P>
