   FINANCIAL
</P>
<P>
   INTERNET-SPEED (Jenkintown, Pa.) _ Much-hyped and long-delayed,
high-speed Internet access is coming to the home, with predictions
that 10 to 16 million households will sign up by 2002. The
experience of the early users offers a glimpse at the Internet's
next frontier, where waiting is rare, dialing in is unnecessary,
and local communications monopolies are for the first time vying
for customers. By Amy Harmon.
</P>
