<HEADER>
A5285 &Cx1f; tad-z
r d &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FOOD-RECIPESWAP29-COX     04-27 0598
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FOOD-RECIPESWAP29-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Atlantan's fudge has withstood the test of time
 &HT;    EDs: Embargoed for Thursday, April 29.
 &HT;    By Marcia Langhenry
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Mildred Peppers of Atlanta sent an old family recipe in response
to Lithonian Samantha Svensson's plea for Buttermilk Fudge, an
unusual blend of buttermilk and all the usual fudge ingredients _
except chocolate.
</P>
<P>
   Peppers said she and her brother used the more than 80-year-old
recipe to make the fudge when they were teenagers. From experience,
she warns cooks to be careful not to let the pot boil over.
</P>
<P>
   DESSERT
</P>
<P>
   Buttermilk Candy
</P>
<P>
   Makes 30 pieces
</P>
<P>
   Preparation time: about 20 minutes
</P>
<P>
   Cooking time: about 15 minutes
</P>
<P>
   Cooling time: 2 hours
</P>
<P>
   You'll get a workout stirring while waiting for this mixture to
boil. But if you don't, it will stick and burn.
</P>
<P>
   2 cups granulated sugar
</P>
<P>
   1 cup buttermilk
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon baking soda
</P>
<P>
   1 cup chopped pecans
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon vanilla extract
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 tablespoons butter
</P>
<P>
   In a large, heavy-bottomed pot, heat sugar, buttermilk and soda
over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until the mixture comes
to a boil. Reduce heat to medium-low and continue to stir until it
reaches soft ball stage (a drop forms a soft ball when dropped into
a small glass of cold water). This should take 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from heat. Stir in nuts, vanilla extract and butter. Beat
with an electric mixer until creamy, about 10 minutes. Pour or
spoon evenly into buttered oblong dish, such as a large loaf pan.
Cool at least 2 hours, then cut in 1-inch squares.
</P>
<P>
   Per piece: 85 calories, 1 gram protein, 3 grams fat (percent
calories from fat, 33), 15 grams carbohydrates, 2 milligrams
cholesterol, 42 milligrams sodium, less than 1 gram fiber.
</P>
