<P>
   BLACK-HAIRPRODUCTS _ Carson Products will soon unveil a new line
of hair coloring products for black women- Dark &AMP; Lovely Diva. The
line, which will be more upscale than other Carson offerings, is
the first product the company has released in about two years. We
talk to Carson marketing folks and analaysts about what it can do
for the company that just yesterday reported its first quarterly
profit in a year. (Poole, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   UPS-EARNINGS _ UPS's profits rose 42 percent in the first
quarter, while revenue rose 8 percent. ``We saw impressive growth
in our express products in most corners of the world,'' said Jim
Kelly, UPS Chairman and CEO. (Thurston, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   WACHOVIA-EARNINGS _ Wachovia Bank is expected to announce the
appointment of Issac Tidwell as president of tits Georgia division.
Wachovia and NationsBank/BankAmerica now will both have minorities
as heads of their Georgia divisions. (Harte, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   MINDSPRING-EARNINGS _ MindSpring releases second quarter
earnings after the bell Tuesday. Results are expected to be good,
but may vary a little because of costs absorbed by Netcom
acquisition in January. (Katz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   PCORDER-EARNINGS _ Releases its first, first quarter earnings
today after the market closes. (Ladendorf, Austin
American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   BELLSOUTH-FINGERS _ATLANTA _ Bell South introduces ``fingers
walking'' cursor on its banner advertising. This is part of the
latest new gimmick in Web design, to have the cursor turn into a
face or whatever. (Katz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   MONEYTALK _ Younger readers frequently ask whether they ought to
fiddle with their investments, now that the stock market is so high
and so wobbly. Sell stocks? Stop putting new money into the market?
Buy only the most conservative stocks? There is, of course, no
simple, concrete and achievable answer for everybody. But there is
a general concept that will lead a lot of neophyte investors to
their own answers: core investments. (Ezell, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   EQUANT _ ATLANTA _Equant, which runs the world's largest data
communications network, is expanding it to offer combined voice and
data service to business customers in Hungary, Ukraine and
Martinique. (Kanell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   PIRACY-PC _ ATLANTA _ Microsoft wants us to steal less of its
software. The company mostly is going after the small and medium
sized businesses knowingly or unwittingly using pirated software.
(Clothier, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
