   BASKETBALL
</P>
<P>
   NBA
</P>
<P>
   BKN-HAWKS _ ATLANTA _ Mookie Blaylock is a high-energy point
guard who often leads the league in steals, but does he play the
position well enough to take the Hawks to a title? Evaluating the
long-term Hawk. (Denberg, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   TENNIS
</P>
<P>
   TEN-RAFTER _ AT&AMP;T Challenge top seed Patrick Rafter of Australia
talks about being a heartthrob and the drawbacks of being famous,
especially among female fans and especially in Australia. He felt
he had absolutely no privacy there, so he moved to Bermuda. He
plays his opening match Tuesday. (Holcomb, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20-22.
</P>
<P>
   RAC-ARCHDEACON-DERBY _ LOUISVILLE, Ky. _ Colorful story on
juiciest topic of the Derby _ cheating, especially the use of
``machines,'' the crude, AAA battery devices some jockeys use to
jolt a horse. Wednesday is the deadline to allow Valhol, the
Arkansas Derby winner into Kentucky Derby. Valhol's jockey, Bill
Patin is accused of using a shocker to help the 31-1 longshot win.
Arkansas Racing Commission has held up $300,000 purse and without
that cash. Valhol likely won't qualify for Derby because of not
enough graded-stakes earnings. (Archdeacon, Dayton Daily News). 30.
</P>
