   YUGOSLAVIA-KOSOVO CONFLICT
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-CONGRESS _ WASHINGTON _ The House is scheduled to vote
Wednesday on U.S. involvement in the Kosovo conflict, leaders said
Tuesday. Votes are planned on whether to invoke the War Powers Act,
which would start the clock on a withdrawal of U.S. forces, and on
a declaration of war against Yugoslavia. The House may also vote on
a bill requiring President Clinton to obtain congressional approval
before sending ground troops to fight in the Balkans. (Malone, Cox
News Service).
