<P>
   ELDERLY-ROBBER _ Follow to Forrest Tucker, the 78-year-old bank
robber: How many PBCo. bank robberies is he suspected of? There
were two guns found in his car. Were they loaded? What did the
Jupiter bank robbery victims think of him? Is his former
partner-in-crime, Mr. Green, still alive, and if so, does he have
anything to say? Who is his girlfriend and what does she have to
say? What's he do for money (assuming he can't live on bank booty)?
Does he get social security? Did he have a particular MO that would
tell us something about him? Like calling the tellers
``sweethearts'' or ``young lady''? (Mossman, Palm Beach Post).
</P>
<P>
   LA-HOUSE _ METAIRIE, La. _ When former U.S. Cong. Bob Livingston
(R-La.) resigned amid scandal on the same day President Clinton was
impeached, folks from every walk of life rushed to fill his shoes.
Among the nine candidates in the May 1 special election: A wizard,
a virgin, and Monica. (Konigsmark, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
MOVED.
