   &UR; CONFLICT IN THE BALKANS &LR;   &UR; (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-STRIKES (Washington) _ Latest information from NATO
paints a so-so picture of the effectiveniess of allied air strikes.
By Fred Kaplan. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   YUGOSLAVIA (Washington) _ Hopes for a swift settlement of the
Balkans crisis fades as envoys fail to bridge the diplomatic gulf
between NATO and Yugoslavia's embattled president. By Bob Hohler.
1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-TALKS (Moscow) _ Western allies put in play their plan to
work with Russia to solve the Yugoslavia crisis, but talks produce
no immediate breakthrough. By David Filipov. 1000 words.
</P>
