<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BLACK-HAIRPRODUCTS-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Carson planning new product launch
 &HT;    By Shelia M. Poole
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Carson Products said Tuesday it plans to unveil a new
hair coloring product this fall, the first new product announcement
in more than a year.
</P>
<P>
   Carson, a Savannah, Ga.-based ethnic beauty products maker,
plans to call the line Dark &AMP; Lovely Diva. Diva will become part of
Carson's highly successful flagship Dark &AMP; Lovely brand.
</P>
<P>
   It will hit store shelves in August or September, said Shawn
Tollerson, marketing director for Dark &AMP; Lovely. Dark &AMP; Lovely
Diva's introduction will be supported by a print and radio
advertising campaign.
</P>
<P>
   Carson commands a 61 percent share of the ethnic hair coloring
market, she said.
</P>
<P>
   The last two product launches for the company ended in
disappointment.
</P>
<P>
   One, a professional line, was discontinued, and a Dark &AMP; Lovely
cosmetic line has had sluggish sales.
</P>
<P>
   ``The name of the game is product and staying ahead of the
competition,'' said Warren Beck, an analyst with New York-based
Cromwell, Miller &AMP; Greer.
</P>
<P>
   The new line will have eight shades with such names as Toffee
Tease, Calypso Candy and Golden Goddess.
</P>
<P>
   Introduction of the new line comes at a critical time for
Carson. On Monday, the company released its first-quarter results,
which showed its first profit in a year. The company reported net
income of $180,000, compared with a loss of $501,000 in the same
period a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
   In the past year, the company has had a management
restructuring, and President Gregory Andrews died while on business
in South Africa. Carson expects its new line to contribute $10
million in sales within the next year, said Chief Financial Officer
Robert Pierce.
</P>
<P>
   Sheila Poole writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution,
Atlanta, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
