<P>
   SALMON-CUTLER (Washington) _ President Clinton names his onetime
legal counsel, Lloyd Cutler, as a special representative to the
U.S.-Canada salmon negotiations. The appointment marks the most
vigorous effort yet by the White House to revive the U.S.-Canada
salmon treaty, which has been mired in controversy since it was
signed in 1985.
