<HEADLINE>
ROENICK TO PRACTICE WITH COYOTES WEDNESDAY 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By TIM TYERS  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ST. LOUIS - Coyotes center Jeremy Roenick said Tuesday he
intends to participate in an optional skate with team members
today, just 13 days after his jaw was broken in three places on a
vicious check by Derian Hatcher in Dallas.
</P>
<P>
   ``I haven't touched a stick since I was hurt,'' said Roenick,
who last week cut the cast off oof his broken right thumb that was
injured seconds before Hatcher's hit. ``I plan to skate more for
conditioning, but I plan to practice with the boys, too.''
</P>
<P>
   Roenick was asked if his planned return to the ice today means
he might be available for a possible second-round series, likely
against Hatcher and the Dallas Stars?
</P>
<P>
   ``Who knows?'' he said. ``It's hard to say. I'll know more after
I see my doctor (Dr. Reed Day) on Thursday. It will be my
second-week checkup since the injury.''
</P>
<P>
   Hatcher was handed a five-game playoff suspension, longest in
league history, for the hit. &QL;
</P>
