<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR WEDNESDAY, APRIL 28
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Wednesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-TIMOR-RDP-NYT (Moved on Sunday, Apr. 25)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, Apr. 25,
about violence in East Timor misstated the year the territory was
annexed by Indonesia. It was 1976, not 1996.
</P>
<P>
   BC-BOOK-TALK-NYT (moved on Wednesday, Apr. 21)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, Apr.
21, about ``Another Life: A Memoir of Other People'' by Michael
Korda, editor in chief at Simon &AMP; Schuster, misstated the number of
American book publishing houses owned by Jews by the late 1920's,
an era in which the author depicts the industry as ``a rather
stuffy and self-important club.'' At least seven had been founded
by Jews by that time, not just one.
</P>
